title: Formation of light nuclei in reactions with B-11 and Ne-20 ions at energies of 18-20 MeV per nucleon.

x4freetext: Formation of light nuclei in reactions with B-11 and
Ne-20 ions at energies of 18-20 MeV per nucleon.

x4codes.hlp: Joint Institute for Nuclear Research (JINR), Dubna

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Izv. Rossiiskoi Akademii Nauk, Ser.Fiz., Vol.52, Issue.11, p.2171 (1988)
Jour: Bull.Russian Academy of Sciences - Physics, Vol.52, Issue.11, p.90 (1988)

x4codes.hlp: Joint Institute for Nuclear Research (JINR), Dubna

x4freetext: Two dE-E telescopes were used. Each
telescope consisted of a silicon dE detector with the
thickness of sensitive layer 60 mu-m and E detector
with a sensitive layer of 2 mm.
Detector was placed at the angle of 10 degrees
changed, STATUS in Sub 044-047 were added.
Ta-181 targets of 2.5 mg/cm2 thickness were used.
